        <p class="p_Comment"><span class="f_TitreReleaseNote">New local variable :</span> A new variable, <span
        class="f_Variables">ComputeForDraw</span>, is added into setup rules. It allows to test if computation is running for the
		frame drawings (<span class="f_Variables">True()</span>) or for components (<span class="f_Variables">False()</span>).</p>

        <p class="p_Comment">It is currently available at outer frame, sash frame, transom, bead frame and composed panel levels, and may be completed soon.</p>

        <p>See also the <a href="ordrecalcul.php">computation sequence</a> at the bottom for more détails.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span class="f_TitreReleaseNote">New local variable :</span> A new variable, <span
        class="f_Variables">PreComp</span>, is added into forulas. It is designed to be able to test when we are into a dimensional pre-computation stage
        (<span class="f_Variables">True()</span>) or when the program process a component computation (<span class="f_Variables">False()</span>).</p>

        <p class="p_Comment">Currently available within the outer frame, sash frame, beads frame, composed panel, peripheral profile and transom, and maybe
		more in the future. Also available within fittings frame, but is always worth <span class="f_Variables">False()</span>.</p>

        <p>See also the <a href="ordrecalcul.php">computation sequence</a> at the bottom for more détails.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span class="f_TitreReleaseNote">New jumping instruction Goto :</span> This <span
        class="f_Variables">Goto</span> instruction allows to jump from the calling formula to the called formula.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment">It can allow for instance to jump the outer frame set up rules, in order to obtain a faster drawing, and to avoid in some cases
		to read variables that are not existing during a <span class="f_Variables">ComputeForDraw</span>.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example:</span></p>

        <p style="text-align: center; text-indent: 45px;"><img
        src="img/clip0902eng.jpg" width="604" height="239" border="0"
        alt="clip0902eng"></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;">

        <table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#bfd7bf"
        border="0"
        style="background-color: #bfd7bf; border: none border-spacing:0px; border-collapse: collapse;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="525"
                style="width: 525px; border: solid 1px #000000;"><p
                class="p_Notes" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 10px;"><span
                class="f_Notes" style="font-weight: bold;">Attention
                !</span><span class="f_Notes"> :</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- It is not allowed to use this instruction within a pre-computation stage (<span
                class="f_Variables">PreComp = True()</span>).</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- The above sample is working correctly as long as NO profile code labelled ENDCOMPUTE is existing !</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- The instruction allows to jump pages of code but always forward, toward the bottom. It is not possible to jump to a
				rule located before the calling rule.</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes" style="color: #ff0000;">- Into a <span class="f_Variables">Goto &lt;Label&gt;</span> instruction, winpro seach for 
				the next page of rule with this label, and stop as soon as found. BUT if the called
				rule is empty, the program won't reach it and the <span class="f_Variables">Goto</span> will ignore it. It is then better to always fill a
				rule into that case, even a comment character, but the called rule mustn't be empty !</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment">This variable is currently into the outer frame, sash frame, beads frame, fittings frame and transom, and probably more to 
		come in the future.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span class="f_TitreReleaseNote">New frame drawing function :</span><span class="f_ImageCaption">The 
		</span><span style="color: #0000ff;">AddShapeNumToDraw (shapeNum, Inside, Outside, Sequence, Origin)</span> function allows to replace the automatique
		WinPro's frame drawing with user defined shapes added. Only available for transom currently.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- shapeNum</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">is the shape number to add.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Inside</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">is worth 1 when shape is visible from the inside, 0 otherwise.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Outside</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">is worth 1 when shape is visible from the outside, 0 otherwise.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Sequence</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
