              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Origin</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">unused currently, value 0.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span class="f_TitreReleaseNote">Sides sequence :</span> The standard WinPro label for a given side would not be relevant for
		some cases, due to new shapes now available.</p>
 

        <p class="p_Comment">Indeed, the user may now create shapes composed of several bottom left sides for a same frame, that is why the current labelling
		of sides is outdated for such designs.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment">Sides will be easier to handle using instead a numbering sequence, clockwise, starting at « 0 ».</p>

        <p class="p_Comment">The side number « 0 » is the one with the slope the nearest from 180°, but always lower than 180°.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment">For instance into a rectangle, the bottom side has an angle of 180°, the left one 90°, the top is 0° and the right is 270°.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment">The first side lower than 180° is then the left side.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment">The <span class="f_Variables">SideIndex</span> variable returns the current side number.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span class="f_TitreReleaseNote">New function GetArraySize ():</span> This <span
        class="f_Variables">GetArraySize ()</span> function is available anywhere at data set up level, and returns the number of cells from an array
		variable, global or local.</p>
 
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 395px;" width="395"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 78px;"><span
                style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">NbFill := </span><span
                style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">GetArraySize (</span><span
                style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">_FillType</span><span
                style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">)</span></p>
              </td>
              <td style="width: 679px;" width="679"><p>returns into variable
                <span class="f_Variables">NbFill</span> the number of cells of the global array variable <span
                class="f_Variables">_FillType</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span class="f_TitreReleaseNote">New function GetDigit () :</span> The <span
        class="f_Variables">GetDigit (Number , Position)</span> may be used at any data set up level, and returns the digit from a number according the
		requested position.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Examples :</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 395px;" width="395"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 78px;"><span
                style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">decade := </span><span
                style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">GetDigit
                (1234.567,1) =&gt; 3</span></p>
              </td>
              <td style="width: 395px;" width="395"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 78px;"><span
                style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">hunderdth := </span><span
                style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">GetDigit
                (1234.567,-2) =&gt; 6</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span class="f_TitreReleaseNote">Enhancement on variables Side and Radius :</span> Both variables are now modifiable and always
		filled by default.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Examples :</span></p>

        <div
