          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 444px;" width="444"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 73px;"><span class="f_Variables">If Side = Top</span></p>

                <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 73px;"><span
                class="f_Variables">  a := </span><span class="f_Variables"
                style="font-weight: bold;">Slope (</span><span
                class="f_Variables">X0, Y0, X1, Y1</span><span
                class="f_Variables" style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>

                <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 73px;"><span
                class="f_Variables">End If</span></p>
              </td>
              <td style="width: 395px;" width="395"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 78px;"><span
                style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">returns into variable <span
                class="f_Variables" style="font-weight: bold;">a</span> the angle of <span class="f_Variables">top</span> side.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><img src="img/embim5.jpg" alt="" border="0"
        height="275" hspace="1" vspace="1" width="530"></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="44"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
              </td>
              <td><span
                style="font-size: 24pt; font-weight: bold;">Overview</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment">WinPro version 9.0.0 introduces a complete rebuild of the shapes computation system, allowing users to compute, draw and produce
		shaped designs difficult or impossible to set up until now.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment">This rebuild of the shape engine has involved the creation of a new set of functions and variables making complex shapes easier
		to implement.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment">Existing variables and functions from previous versions are still available, meaning that existing data set up are fully
		compatible with version 9.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment">The particular cases of incompatibility (variable name changes, behaviour changes, .) will be detailled into the following and
		next release note, when required.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment">Those functions and variables are available at any data set up level for a window code. Either they are initialized by WinPro
		according shape information input (global shape and dimension, outer frame or sash frame sections, .), and may then be loaded and used into data set
		up, or they are freely defined by user.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment">The shapes handled may be closed or opened, simple or complex, but are always composed of straight or curved segments.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment">In order to be trained to use this new concept of set up, this manual will be laid with a <a href="9_0_0_xExample1.php">complete
		sample of data set up</a> using the new shape features. The miscellaneous function sets will also be listed at the end of the document.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 60px; padding: 0px; text-align: middle; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="44"></td>
              <td
                style="text-align:center;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;"><span
                style="font-size: 22pt; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(120, 120, 120); text-decoration: underline;">List of new variables and 
				functions</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="44"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
              </td>
              <td><span
                style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;"></span><br>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="44"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
              </td>
              <td><a name="ch2"></a><span
                style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Basic notions</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="44"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
              </td>
              <td><span
                style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;"></span><br>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>In order to handle easier this new data set up concept for shapes computation, some reminders and additional vocabularies are detailed into this
		chapter.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;">Type of side</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>Sides are either simple or complex.</p>

        <p>When simple, they may be straight or arched.</p>

        <p>When complex, they are composed of « Sub - Sides » that are always simple.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;">Standard WinPro side feature</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

        <p>This is the usual WinPro side <span
        class="f_Variables">Top</span>, <span class="f_Variables">Bottom</span>,
        <span class="f_Variables">Left</span>, <span
        class="f_Variables">Right</span>, <span
        class="f_Variables">TopLeft</span>, <span
        class="f_Variables">TopRight</span> as well as <span
        class="f_Variables">BottomLeft</span> and <span
        class="f_Variables">BottomRight</span>. Usual label for each side is also assigned with a numeric value varying according the frame where the code is
		located.</p>

        <p>Those sides are simple or complex.</p>

        <p>The <span class="f_Variables">Side</span> variable returns the name of the current side computed.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;">Segment</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>A segment is either straight or arched, that the smallest element of a shape.</p>

        <p>Equivalent to the « Sub - Side » notion, but more generic.</p>

        <p>For instance, a free shape within WpReport module may not have « side » nor « sub-side », but may be only composed of segments.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;">Sub-Side</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>A « Sub - Side » is either straight or arched, that is the smallest element of a shape.</p>

        <p>A « Sub - Side » is a segment.</p>

        <p>A « Sub - Side » always belongs to a side.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;">Shape array</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>The shape array is an array where the various shapes that will be computed may be stored and reuse when necessary. Into data set up it is possible
		to store 1000 shapes into the array of shapes, from n°1 to n°1000. The shape array is not reset between the pre-computation and component computation,
		allowing to "transfer" information.</p>

        <p>Into WpReport, it is possible to set a user defined array size. See function « <span
        class="f_Variables">CreerTableauForme ()</span> ». </p>

        <p>Attention, a too big shape array will require memory when not necessary.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;">Target shape</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>Using any function returning a shape, the user may give the target shape number, or else set that winpro should store the shape into the first
		available cell of the array.</p>

        <p>For the first case, the user just send the number of the shape to the function (or a variable containing the index). Take care anyway not to
		override an existing shape.</p>

        <p>Variable « <span class="f_Variables">LastCreatedShapeNum</span> » remains then unchanged.</p>

        <p>For the second case, setting value <span class="f_Variables">« -1 »</span> will imply Winpro to use the first cell(s) available.</p>

        <p>Variable « <span class="f_Variables">LastCreatedShapeNum</span> », which is an array variable, returns the index of the last shape(s) created.
		When the function used before the variable creates a single shape, only the first cell of the array variable is used, otherwise the program will use
		as many cells as shapes generated.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="44"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
              </td>
              <td><span
                style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">List of predefined shapes variables</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="44"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
              </td>
              <td><span
                style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;"></span><br>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Those shapes are generated by WinPro's computation. They represent for example the shape of a frame, of a profile... They are not automatically
		loaded by WinPro to avoid a useless computation.</p>

        <p>We then have to use a dedicated « <span class="f_Variables">LoadShape()</span> » instruction to load a shape into memory. See chapter about
		functions for creating and modifying shape lower for more details about this function, its syntax and usage.</p>

        <p>Below is the list of predefined shape variable available:</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;">Shapes related to the outer frame</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">_OutOuterFrameShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for the outside edge of the outer frame. No additional setting required.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example:</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 495px;" width="495"><p class="p_Comment"
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 68px;"><span
                class="f_Variables">LoadShape (- 1, </span><span
                class="f_Variables"
                style="font-weight: bold;">_OutOuterFrameShapeNum</span><span
                class="f_Variables">)</span></p>
              </td>
              <td style="width: 579px;" width="579"><p>load the outside shape of the outer frame into the first available cell of the shape array.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">_InsOuterFrameShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for the inside edge of the outer frame. No additional setting required.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">_ExtendedOuterFrameShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for false arches.</p>

        <p>The first setting correspond to the side number, the second one is unused. The third setting allows to define if is considered the smaller height
		(inside view) = 2 or larger height (outside view) = 1. Attention, setting 3 = 2 (smaller height or inside view) is only available for a false 
		arch of type 1.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example: </span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 581px;" width="581"><p class="p_Comment"
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
                class="f_Variables">LoadShape (- 1, <span
                style="font-weight: bold;">_ExtendedOuterFrameShape</span>,
                SideIndex,,1)</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">_InputOuterFrameShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for the outside edge of the outer frame, without considering the false arch, if there was no false arch. No additional setting required. That's the shape as input into Dimensions tab.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">_InputExtOuterFrameShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for the inside edge of the outer frame, without considering the false arch, if there was no false arch. No additional setting required. That's the shape as input into Dimensions tab.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span
              class="f_Variables">_MasInputOuterFrameShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for the inside edge of the outer frame, without considering the false arch, if there was no false arch. No additional setting required. That's the shape as input into Dimensions tab, into masonry mode.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;">Shapes related to the sash frame</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">_OutSashFrameShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for outside edge of the sash frame currently computed. Attention, this is outside edge of sash frame and not of a single leaf.</p>

        <p>No additional setting required.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span
              class="f_Variables">_OutSashFrameLeafShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for outside edge of leaves from the sash frame currently computed, with a second setting used for the leaf index. Setting 1 
		remains unused here.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 581px;" width="581"><p class="p_Comment"
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
                class="f_Variables">LoadShape (- 1, <span
                style="font-weight: bold;">_OutSashFrameLeafShape</span>,,
                Leaf)</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span
                class="f_Variables">_OutInputSashFrameLeafShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for outside edge of leaves from the sash frame currently computed, without considering a potential false arch. The second setting 
		is used for the leaf index. Setting 1 remains unused here.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span
              class="f_Variables">_InsSashFrameLeafShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for the inside edge of leaves from the sash frame, with a second setting for the leaf index. Setting 1 remains unused here.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example : </span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 581px;" width="581"><p class="p_Comment"
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
                class="f_Variables">LoadShape (- 1, <span
                style="font-weight: bold;">_InsSashFrameLeafShape</span>,,
                Leaf)</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span
              class="f_Variables">_SashFalseArchShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for false arches.</p>

        <p>The first setting is for the side index, the second for leaf index, the third one is used to set if the shape considered is from the inside = 2 
		or outside = 1.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
                class="f_Variables">LoadShape (- 1, </span><span
                class="f_Variables"
                style="font-weight: bold;">_SashFalseArchShape</span><span
                class="f_Variables">, SideIndex, Leaf,2)</span></p>
              </td>
              <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;">Shapes related to fittings frame</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span
              class="f_Variables">_OutFittingsFrameLeafShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable corresponding to the outside of each leaf of a fittings frame for the current sash, the second setting is the leaf index. First
		setting remains unused.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;">Shapes related to transoms</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;"> </span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">_OutTransomShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for the outside edge of the current transom, the visible side of the transom viewed from outside.</p>

        <p>No additional settings required.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">_InsTransomShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for the inside edge of the current transom, the visible side of the transom viewed from inside without rebates (only smaller height
		is seen).</p>

        <p>No additional settings required.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">_TotTransomShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Shape variable for current transom, transom viewed from inside including rebates, the « length » is defined from the transom receiving it, 
		without rebate. Or else, profile length before any join operation, or width of outside view with length of inside view.</p>

        <p>No additional settings required.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example:</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
                class="f_Variables">LoadShape (- 1, </span><span
                class="f_Variables"
                style="font-weight: bold;">_TotTransomShape</span><span
                class="f_Variables">)</span></p>
              </td>
              <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;">Shapes related to fillings</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">_BeadsShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Variable for beads frame shape (without rebates).</p>

        <p>The second setting is for the filling index.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
                class="f_Variables">LoadShape (- 1, </span><span
                class="f_Variables"
                style="font-weight: bold;">_BeadsShape</span><span
                class="f_Variables">,,FillingIndex)</span></p>
              </td>
              <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">_FillingShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Variable for filling shape, clearance deduced.</p>

        <p>The second setting is for the filling index.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
                class="f_Variables">LoadShape (- 1, </span><span
                class="f_Variables"
                style="font-weight: bold;">_FillingShape</span><span
                class="f_Variables">,,FillingIndex)</span></p>
              </td>
              <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;">Formes
        liées Profils périphériques</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">_PeripheralProfileShape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Development in progress, will be documented soon.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold;">Label</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>For various functions, « labels » for sides of the shape may be used.</p>

        <p>This mainly for shapes representing profiles.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>It is possible to use labels with following codes:</p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">1000</span> = start</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">2000</span> =
              outside</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">3000</span> = end</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">4000</span> =
              inside</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>The following variables may also be used into data set up:</p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&bull;</span></td>
