        </table>
        </div>

        <p style="text-align: center; text-indent: 45px;"><img
        src="img/clip0903eng.jpg" width="542" height="410" border="0"
        alt="clip0903eng"></p>

        <p><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline">Same for settings from 11 to 17</span>, (Setting 11 for side 1, Setting 12 for side 2,
		..., for a total of 8 sides possible into WinPro, from 0 to 7).</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="44"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
              </td>
              <td><a name="ch1"></a><span
                style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">WinPro creation and modification functions for shapes</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>Those functions are designed to create and hadle shapes from the shape array, as an extension of existing functions for such features into composed
		panels, as detailed into <a href="rn642x.php">release note version 6.4.24</a>.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">LoadShape (Target shape number, Predefined shape code, Setting1, Setting2, Setting3)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Function to load a shape defined within data set up. See previous chapter about predefined variables.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Target shape number</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Refer to basic notions.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Predefined shape code</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">See list of variables of predefined shapes for current frame, for instance <span
                class="f_Variables">_OutOuterFrameShape</span>.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Setting 1, 2 and 3</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">According the shape to be loaded, several settings maybe needed, as leaf index. Refer to predefined shapes list 
				for details.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;">

        <table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#bfd7bf"
        border="0"
        style="background-color: #bfd7bf; border: none border-spacing:0px; border-collapse: collapse;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="525"
                style="width: 525px; border: solid 1px #000000;"><p
                class="p_Notes" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 10px;"><span
                class="f_Notes" style="font-weight: bold;">Note</span><span
                class="f_Notes"> :</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- When the function returns several shapes (e.g. list of false arch shapes), the target shape is automatically set to
				« -1 » value, corresponding to first available slots into shape array.</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- Setting 3 is only used in case of false arch shape and allows selection of a view type (inside or outside).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Exemple :</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
                style="font-weight: bold;">LoadShape (</span><span
                class="f_Variables">- 1, _FillingShape,,
                FillingIndex</span><span class="f_Variables"
                style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>
              </td>
              <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>Loads the global filling dimension clearance deduced, into the first available slot from the shape array. Refer to predefined shape variables for
		details about variable <span class="f_Variables">_FillingShape</span>.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">CreateShape (Index of target shape to create, Shape name [, Orientation], DimA, DimB, ., DimL)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>2 versions of the instruction exist, this is the detail for standard version.</p>

        <p>It allows creation of free shapes (different from predefined) anywhere into the set up (Except WinPro drawings. Similar to shape handling functions
		into composed panels. See <a href="rn642x.php">release note version 6.4.24</a>).</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Index of target shape to create</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Slot into the shape array, -1 for first available slot.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape name</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">For instance <span
                class="f_Variables">Rectangle</span>, <span
                class="f_Variables">Trapzium</span>. See <a
                href="rn642x.php">release note version 6.4.24</a>.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Orientation</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape orientation according shape, values <span class="f_Variables">Left</span> or 
				<span class="f_Variables">Right</span>.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- DimA to DimL</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Various dimensions to input for a given shape. See <a href="rn642x.php">release note version
                6.4.24</a>.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
                style="font-weight: bold;">CreateShape (</span><span
                class="f_Variables">- 1, Rectangle, 1000, 1000</span><span
                class="f_Variables" style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>
              </td>
              <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>This instruction loads a rectangle with dimensions 1000x1000 into the first available slot of the shape array.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">CreateShape (Shape nbr to be created, -77, trapezium number)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Creates trapezium shapes required from a computation of arches using functions <span
        class="f_Variables">BOWCUTxxx ()</span>. See <a href="rn722x.php">release note
        version 7.2.29</a>.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape nbr to be created</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Slot within shape array, -1 for first available slot.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- -77</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Switch to allow fetching data from trapezium computation of a <span
                class="f_Variables">BOWCUTxxx ()</span> function.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Trapezium number</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Trapezium umber to copy as separate shape. Note that the first trapezium is indexed 0.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 1000px;" width="1000"><p class="p_Comment"
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
                style="font-weight: bold;"></span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"># Variables initialization</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">angleBD := 90</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">angleBF := 90</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">ray := 500</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">pX0 := 0</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">pY0 := 100</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">pX1 := 1000</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">pY1 := 100</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">ox := 500</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">oy := 100</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">pdx := 0</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">pdy := 0</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">pfx := 0</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">pfy := 0</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">ep := 80</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"># Initialization of computation for trapezium number into the bow (see <a href="rn722x.php">release note version
        7.2.29</a>)</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">a := BOWCUTInit ()</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">a := BOWCUTSetUsualWidths (50, 100,
        150, 200, 250, 300, 400, 500, 800, 1000)</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">a := BOWCUTPenalty (2000)</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">a := BOWCUTDefineTmpBow (pX0, pY0, pX1,
        pY1, ox, oy, ray, ep, 0)</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">a := BOWCUTAddBow ()</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"># Trapezium number targeted set up (refer to release note 7.2.29)</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmpNumArc := 5</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">a := BOWCUTSetNbTrapeziums
        (tmpNumArc)</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"># Computation of trapezium sub shapes into the bow</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">i := 0</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">Repeat While i &lt;
        tmpNumArc</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 80px;"><span
        style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">CreateShape
        (</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">110 + i, - 77,
        i</span><span
        style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">)</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 80px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">i += 1</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">End Repeat</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Drawing set up :</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">PenColour (_OuterFrameIntLineColourRed, _OuterFrameIntLineColourGreen, _OuterFrameIntLineColourBlue)</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">Brush (Colour, Green)</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">Number (100, 50, tmpNumArc + 100)</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">i := 0</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">Repeat While i &lt;
        tmpNumArc</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 80px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">StartPath ()</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 80px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">DrawShape (TmpNumForme + i, 0,
        0)</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 80px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">EndPath ()</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 80px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">FillAndBorderPath ()</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 80px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">i += 1</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">End Repeat</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img
        src="img/sssclip13.jpg" alt="sssClip13" border="0" height="292"
        width="548"></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">CreateProfileShape (shapeNum to create,
                Segment table, leftThickness, rightThickness, AngleSL,
                angleSR, CutS, offsetS, AngleEL, angleER, cutE,
                offsetE)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Allows to create a profile shape with the same way as a "DS" drawing. The second setting is an array variable containing (x,y) coordinates and
		radius for the "axis" segment. The content of the table corresponds to the one used for the instruction 
		<span class="f_Variables">SetupShapeInfo</span> (5 settings).</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 1400px;" width="1400"><p class="p_Comment"
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
                style="font-weight: bold;">CreateProfileShape (</span><span
                class="f_Variables">- 1, gms, SmallerHeight / 2.0,
                SmallerHeight / 2.0, Angle1, 180 - Angle1, 0, 0, Angle2, 180 -
                Angle2, 0, 0</span><span class="f_Variables"
                style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">DeleteShape (Index of the shape to delete into the shape array)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Suitable for unloading a shape from memory, deleting a given shape from the shape array. As for an example, at the end of a routine it may be
		useful to delete unnecessary shapes for drawings from shapes required from a given set up.</p>

        <p>Anyway, WinPro always deletes the array content at the end of computation, but this instruction may be useful to free some more slots during
		computation.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color:       rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">CopyShape (Source shape, Target shape)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Copy from a source shape to a target shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape to be copied.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Target shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of the shape that will be created.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
                style="font-weight: bold;">CopyShape (</span><span
                class="f_Variables">_OutOuterFrameShape, - 1</span><span
                class="f_Variables" style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>This code copies the outside of outer frame shape (refer to list of predefined shapes above, <span
        class="f_Variables">_OutOuterFrameShape</span>) into a traget shape at the first available shape from the shape array (refer to basic notions 
		above).</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">RectangleIncludingShape (shapeNum[, Smallest, [NearestAngle]])</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

Example :


This instruction transforms shape number 2 from the shape array (full bow) into rectangle, the original full bow shape is overwritten.
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>Transformation of a given shape into a rectangle including this shape. Maybe used with 1 up to 3 settings.</p>

        <p>Remarque, si utilisé avec un seul paramètre, les labelles sont
        incohérent.</p>

        <p><span style="font-style: italic;">- shapeNum</span> : Index of the shape to be transformed into a rectangle containing the shape.</p>

        <p><span style="font-style: italic;">- Smallest</span> : When left to 0, WinPro will evaluate the function as a single setting instruction. 
		Otherwise, when set to value 1, WinPro computes for smallest rectangle containing the shape, and the nearest rectangle from the slope with side 
		of label 2000 (outside). When set to value 2, WinPro computes for the rectangle incluiding the shape with the slope of side 2000 (outside) that 
		forces the computation (or the thrid setting).</p>

        <p><span style="font-style: italic;">- NearestAngle</span> : Unused field in case setting 2 is worth 0. In this case; WinPro does no more compute
		using slope of label 2000 to find the rectangle slope, but computes using supplied value. This allows to search for the smallest rectangle without
		reversing width and height, in case of a shape with no label. When the second setting is worth 2, the angle is assigned, the program does no more
		compute the smallest containing rectangle, but the smallest rectangle for this angle.</p>

        <p>Thgis function completes variable <span
        class="f_Variables">ShapeInfo []</span> at cells 23, 24 and 30.
        Only when the second setting exists and is not null, otherwise the rectangle has an angle of 0° and boundaries are known, so that variables are no
		more necessary.</p>

        <p><span style="font-style: italic;">- ShapeInfo [23]</span> : Length
        / Width of the rectangle.</p>

        <p><span style="font-style: italic;">- ShapeInfo [24]</span> :
        Thickness / Height of the rectangle.</p>

        <p><span style="font-style: italic;">- ShapeInfo [30]</span> : Rotation angle of the rectangle.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img
        src="img/clip3-1eng.jpg" alt="Clip3-1eng" border="0" height="242"
        width="316"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>This instruction transforms shape number 2 from the shape array (full bow) into rectangle, the original full bow shape is overwritten.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">TransformShape (shapeNum, Transformation type, p1, p2, p3, p4)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>Operates a transformation of the defined shape into another shape, using a translation, a proportional transformation, a rotation or a symmetry.</p>

        <p>Only specified Px settings are to be used, as an example for a type 1, do not leave the 2 last commas.</p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- shapeNum</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of the shape to be transformed.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Transformation type</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption"></span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">1 : Translation using a vector (0,0), (p1, p2).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">2 : Proportional transformation of center (x,y) and factor (Fx, Fx). Uses settings p1, p2, p3.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">3 : Rotation of center (x,y)  and angle A. Uses settings p1, p2, p3.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">4 : Orthogonal symmetry based on line crossing points (x1,y1) and (x2,y2). Uses settings p1, p2, p3, p4.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">5 : Centrral symmetry of center (x1,y1). Uses settings p1, p2. This is equivalent to a proportional transformation
				(x1,y1,-1,-1), using settings p1, p2, p3, p4.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">CutShape (Source shape number, Left target shape number, Right target shape number, Angle, X Point, 
			  Y Point, Offset, Thickness)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Cuts a shape according a given line.</p>

        <p>Anyway, be carefull when a closed shape is cut, the line should have 2 and only 2 crossing point with the shape. In case of opened shape, 1 point
		is enough.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape number</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape index that will be cut into the shape array.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Left target shape number</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Number of the left hand shape from the line that will be created for closed shape, or the start of an opened 
				shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Right target shape number</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Number of the right hand shape from the line that will be created for closed shape, or the end of an opened 
				shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Angle</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Inclination of the segment cutting the shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- X point</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">X coordinate of the point where the line crosses. (Into global bench mark).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Y point</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Y coordinate of the point where the line crosses. (Into global bench mark).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Offset</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Segment offset perpendicularly to itself (with an offset, the segment do not crosses XY coordinate anymore). Positive =
				on the right, Negative = on the left.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Thickness</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Segment thickness (like a saw blade), centered to the segment. No negative value allowed.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"># Loading shape of global filling</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">LoadShape (- 1,
        _FillingShapeNum,, FillingIndex)</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"> </span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"># Storage of index of created shape into temporary variable</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">TmpGlobalPanelShapeNum := LastCreatedShapeNum [1]</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"> </span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"># Step 1: sub shape creation, base shape is cut into two shapes</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">CutShape
        (</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">TmpGlobalPanelShapeNum, -
        1, - 1, 45, _FillX [FillingIndex], _FillY [FillingIndex] +
        _FillHeight [FillingIndex]/2, 0, 0</span><span
        style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">)</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"> </span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"># Storage of sub shapes indexes into temporary variables</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">TmpLeftPanelShapeNum:= LastCreatedShapeNum [1]</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">TmpRightPanelShapeNum:= LastCreatedShapeNum [2]</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>This code cuts a filling shape (<span
        class="f_Variables">TmpGlobalPanelShapeNum</span>, voir la première
        instruction <span class="f_Variables">LoadShape ()</span>) instruction) by a segment of position <span class="f_Variables">(X,Y)</span> 
		where X="bottom left corner" of the filling, Y=Height/2 half a filling height. Both sub shapes generated are stored into the first available slot of
		the shape array (values -1).</p>

        <p>Temporary variable <span class="f_Variables">TmpLeftPanelShapeNum</span> stores the left sub shape index into the shape array (variable <span
        class="f_Variables">LastCreatedShapeNum [1]</span>), variable <span class="f_Variables">TmpRightPanelShapeNum</span> stores the right sub shape index
		(variable <span class="f_Variables">LastCreatedShapeNum [2]</span>).</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
