			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">ShrinkShape (Shape index, Value, Label)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Variant of previous function suitable to apply a shrink operation based onto the "Label" of a side. This allows to shrink a profile shape onto the
		start, the outside, the end or the inside.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape index:</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape to be shrinked.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Value</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shrink value if positive, expand value if negative.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Label</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Label of the side(s) where the shrink is applied.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">ExpandShape (Shape index, [Global shrink or Table of values or Shrink by side])</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Expands the defined shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape index:</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape to be expanded.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Global shrink</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Expand value for all sides.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;">or</p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption"> </span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Table of values</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Table of 8 expand values for each side.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;">or</p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption"> </span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shrink by side</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">List of expand values (bottom, top, left, right, topleft, topright, bottomleft, bottomright).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">DeductShape (Source shape, Shape to deduct)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Deduct a defined shape from a source shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape to be modified, this shape will be overwritten.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape to deduct</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape that will be used as a mask.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;">

        <table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#bfd7bf"
        border="0"
        style="background-color: #bfd7bf; border: none border-spacing:0px; border-collapse: collapse;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="525"
                style="width: 525px; border: solid 1px #000000;"><p
                class="p_Notes" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 10px;"><span
                class="f_Notes" style="font-weight: bold;">Note</span><span
                class="f_Notes"> :</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- It is not possible to deduct a shape when included into another (make a hole).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
		style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr align="left" valign="top">
			  <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
				style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">DeductShape (</span><span
				class="f_Variables">1, 2</span><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>
			  </td>
			  <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
			  </td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>According below drawing, the source shape A is stored into shape array at index 1, the shape to be deducted is stored at index 1, the result shape
		C will be stored at index 1.</p>

		<p class="p_Comment" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img
		src="img/clip4-1.zoom60.jpg" alt="Clip4-1" border="0" height="298" width="319"></p>


        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">MergeShape (Source shape, Shape to merge)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Merge a defined shape to a source shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">The shape where the merge operation will be done, this shape will be modified.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape to merge</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape that will be merged to the first one. Attention, both shapes should share at least one segment.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;">

        <table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#bfd7bf"
        border="0"
        style="background-color: #bfd7bf; border: none border-spacing:0px; border-collapse: collapse;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="525"
                style="width: 525px; border: solid 1px #000000;"><p
                class="p_Notes" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 10px;"><span
                class="f_Notes" style="font-weight: bold;">Attention</span><span
                class="f_Notes"> :</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- Both shapes should share at least one common segment!</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
		style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr align="left" valign="top">
			  <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
				style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">MergeShape (</span><span
				class="f_Variables">1, 2</span><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>
			  </td>
			  <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
			  </td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>According below drawing, source shape A is stored into shape array at index 1, the B shape to merge is stored at index 2, and result shape is
		stored at index 1.</p>

		<p class="p_Comment" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img src="img/untitled.jpg"
		alt="Untitled" border="0" height="305" width="183"></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">IntersectionShape (Source shape, Shape to merge)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Merge a defined shape to a source shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape where the intersection is operated, this shape will be modified.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape to merge</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">The shape that will be merged with the first one.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
		style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr align="left" valign="top">
			  <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
				style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">IntersectionShape (</span><span
				class="f_Variables">1, 2</span><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>
			  </td>
			  <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
			  </td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>According below drawing, source shape A is stored into the index 1 of the shape array, shape to merge B is stored at index 2, and result shape at
		index 1.</p>

		<p class="p_Comment" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img src="img/embim6.jpg"
		alt="" border="0" height="297" hspace="1" vspace="1" width="229"></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div
		style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="44"><span
				style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
			  </td>
			  <td><span
				style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">WinPro functions for creation and modification of shape filling 
				« FWL »</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>Those functions allow to compute fillings (glass units, panels, security bars.) of shapes created by previous functions defined, as it is 
		possible using functions FWL detailed into <a href="rn710x.php">release note version 7.1.00</a> (refer to FWL manual into main chm help file).</p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">CuttingFWLShape (Source shape index, Start target shape index, Angle, X, Y, CoefOffset, StartFlag, Thickness1,
			  Thickness2, Clamp1, Clamp2, NbBoardForced, SpacingMin, SpacingMax)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>This function defines filling options of a defined shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape index that needs to be filled using fillinf instructions (FWLs).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Start target shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of the shape for the first board or bar.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Angle</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Angle of the filling, between -89.9° and 90°.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- X</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Coordinate X of the reference point. Should be set only when StartFlag = 1, left value 0 otherwise.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Y</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Coordinate Y of the reference point. Should be set only when StartFlag = 1, left value 0 otherwise.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- CoefOffset </span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Coefficient allowing to modify the reference of start point proportionally to the dimension of board of thickness 1.
				Value between 1 and -1.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- StartFlag</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Reference point for position of the first board:</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 1 for point of coordinates {x,y}.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 2 for center of shape (difference between the uppest and lowest point, between the most on the left and
				the most on the right).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 3 reference point is the most on the left.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 4 reference point is the most on the right.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* In case of negative value (-1, -2, -3, and -4), the shape is filled with bars instead of boards.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Thickness1</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Thickness of the first board or bar type.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Thickness2</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Thickness of second board type or of the space between bars in case of security bar.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Clamp1</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Clamping value for boards of the first type.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Clamp2</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">lamping value for boards of the second type, otherwise should be left null.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- NbBoardForced</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Forces the number of final boards, otherwise should be left null.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- SpacingMin</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Minimum spacing between 2 bars, otherwise should be left null.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- SpacingMax</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Maximum spacing between 2 bars, otherwise should be left null.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div
		style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="44"><span
				style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
			  </td>
			  <td><span
				style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">WinPro function for cutting into sections a finished profile (shape)
				(!!! Enhancement of "BOWCut" functions !!!).</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p class="p_Comment"><span
		style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

		<p>Those functions are suitable to easier compute a bow cutting without various limitations. It is now possible to have bow parts and straight parts
		along onto the shape to cut, as well as concave and convex bows. See also functions <span class="f_Variables">BOWCutxxx ()</span> as defined into 
		<a href="rn722x.php">release note version 7.2.29</a>.</p>

		<p class="p_Comment"><span
		style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

		<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Those functions complete the following variables:</span><span>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17">
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">NbTrapeziumsCut -&gt; </span><span
				style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Number of trapeziums computed by the function.</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17">
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">AngleCutTrapezium -&gt; </span><span
				style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Array variable returning the slope of each trapezium. This allows to run a
				<span class="f_Variables">"GetBoardShapeInfo"</span> instruction easier to obtain the whole data from the trapezium.</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17">
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">CutShapeNum -&gt; </span><span
				style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';">With the 10 settings version, this variable returns the index of shpe cutting
				created. The size of the array variable retuns the number of cutting sequences (or <span class="f_Variables">"NbTrapeziumsCut"</span> -
				1). </span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">4 possible syntaxes (7, 9, 10 and
		11 settings):</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">CutShapeIntoTrapeziums with 7
		settings:</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">CutShapeIntoTrapeziums (Source shape, Start destination shape, Nb trapezium mini, Nb trapezium
				maxi, Optimization time, Length mini, Penality)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>The most simple version, according a shape, the shape is cut with a number of trapeziums included between two limits.</p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of the shape to be cut into trapeziums. A closed shape with correct "labels" for the different sides is 
				required.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Start destination shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of the shape for the first computed trapezium (usually "-1"). May be left empty ",," to avoid storing 
				the trapezium shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Nb trapezium mini</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Minimum number of trapeziums to be obtained as a result. When mini = le maxi, the number of trapezium is 
				forced.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Nb trapezium maxi</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Maximum number of trapeziums to be obtained as a result. When mini = le maxi, the number of trapezium is 
				forced.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Optimization time</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">This value is set for the computation time available for each trapezium assembly. The minimum value is 1, 
				and there is no maximum value. Anyway for a modern computer, above a value of 50, the computation time start being disturbing for the 
				user.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Length mini</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Minimum length of a trapezium that is required, or average between outside and inside lengths of the 
				trapezium.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Penality</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Coefficient computed between the trapeziums surface and the surface of the shape to be cut. The weaker is the value,
				the most wastes are limited and then the greater the number of trapezium will be. (penality = 0 -&gt; for the maximum number of trapeziums). A
				safe basis is estimated to a value of 5000.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">CutShapeIntoTrapeziums with 9
		settings:</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">CutShapeIntoTrapeziums (Source shape, Start destination shape, Nb trapezium mini, Nb trapezium
				maxi, Optimization time, Length mini, Penality, Number standard heights, List standard heights)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Same instruction as with 7 settings with the use of a standard list of trapezium "heights".</p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2000" style="width: 2000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- See previous instructions for the details of the 7 first settings.</span></p>
              </td>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Number standard heights</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Number of cells into the table of standard heights, from first cell to the indicated one. This allows to have a 
				table of value with a big size without using all cells.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- List standard heights</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Array variable representing standard heights to consider. Attention, the list should be sorted crescent 
				sequence imperatively.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">CutShapeIntoTrapeziums with 10
		settings:</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">CutShapeIntoTrapeziums (Source shape, Start destination shape, Nb trapezium mini, Nb trapezium
				maxi, Optimization time, Length mini, Penality, Number standard heights, List standard heights, Store cutting axis)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Same instruction as previously with storing into memory the cutting axis. Useful to be able to re use the same cutting axis for different frames
		(to align cuts between outer frame and sash frame for instance). To use this instruction without standard heigths, leave settings 8 and 9 at 
		value ",,".</p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2000" style="width: 2000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- See previous instructions for the details of the 9 first settings.</span></p>
              </td>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Store cutting axis</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">With a value of 1, WinPro stores the cutting edges shapes (cutting segments). The 
				<span class="f_Variables">"CutShapeNum"</span> variable returns the list of created shapes.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">CutShapeIntoTrapeziums with 11
		settings:</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">CutShapeIntoTrapeziums (Source shape, Start destination shape, Nb trapezium mini, Nb trapezium
				maxi, Optimization time, Length mini, Penality, Number standard heights, List standard heights, Number of cutting axis, Cutting axis 
				table)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>This is a different instruction where the cutting axis are "imposed", several settings are then useless (see detail below).
		The other settings are still used here. The final cutting correspond to the best to the required axis, but not exactly. Indeed, WinPro cannot obtain a
		unique trapezium section and force the cutting axis, axis are then computed for the best result possible.</p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of the shape to be cut into trapeziums. A closed shape with correct "labels" for the different sides is 
				required.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Start destination shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of the shape for the first computed trapezium (usually "-1"). May be left empty ",," to avoid storing 
				the trapezium shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Nb trapezium mini</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">!!! Leave blank with this syntax !!!</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Nb trapezium maxi</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">!!! Leave blank with this syntax !!!</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
