        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div
		style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="44"><span
				style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
			  </td>
			  <td><span
				style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">WinPro function for shape definition</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>Those instructions allow to modify shape, segment by segment. 2 existing syntaxes, with 4 or 5 settings.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Instruction with 4 settings :</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">SetupShapeInfo (Shape index, Absolute segment index, Modification type, Value)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>This version with 4 settings is designed to set up or modify many settings from a segment.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
 
        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of shape to be modified.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Absolute segment index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Segment index without relationship with a given side. For instance into basket handle shape with 3 centers, segments of
				the bow are n° 1, 2 and 3, starting at 0 with left side.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Modification type</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Type of modification to operate. Attention, modification must be granted first for the shape (type « -200 »), and must
				be finalized with closing shape set up (type « -100 »).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 0 : Number of absolute segments.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 1 : Segment type (0 for straight, 1 for arch, 3 for ellipse).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 2 : X0 of segment.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 3 : Y0 of segment.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 4 : X1 of segment.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 5 : Y1 of segment.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 6 : X of the arch center or of the first arch center in case of ellipse.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 7 : Y of the arch center or of the first arch center in case of ellipse.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 8 : X of the second arch center for an ellipse.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 9 : Y of the second arch center for an ellipse.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 10 : Arch radius.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 11 : Value « 0 » for an arch segment, « 1 » for a circle (Bull eye).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 12 : Arch rotation. « 1 » for anticlockwise, « 0 » for clockwise.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* -9 : Sets if the shape is opened (1) or closed (0).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* -10 : Forces or not the locking of position for computation. Remains unused usually, may corrupt
				computation in case of bad use.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 28 : Defines a label for a segment (sub side in absolute), allows to fix an information to name a side for
				instance.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 29 : Side label, Winpro side name. Useful to name sides in case of shrink for instance. See function 
				<span class="f_Variables">ShapeSideInfo ()</span>.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* -200 : Allows shape modification.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* -100 : Finalize the shape set up.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"># Creation of a shape</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
		style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">CreateShape (- 1, CompleteBasketHandle, 1000, 1000,
		300)</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span 
		style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"># Loading into a variable of shape index within shape array</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
		style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">TempShape := LastCreatedShapeNum [1]</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span 
		style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"># Shape modification granted</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
		style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">SetupShapeInfo
		(</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">TempShape, 0, - 200,
		0</span><span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">)</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Instruction with 5 settings :</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">SetupShapeInfo (Shape index, Segment index, , InfoOperation, TabSeg)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>This instruction is designed to integrate, replace. a segment. Attention, a 4 settings syntax instruction is needed before and after to grant and
		close modification, grant modification with type « -200 » then finalize with closing shape definition with type « -100 ».</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
 
        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape number</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape to be modified.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Segment number</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Segment number to be modified in absolute, corresponds to absolute sub side number.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
		  <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Unused, leave this setting empty.</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption"> </span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- InfoOperation</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Operation type.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 0 to add a segment at the end (« segment n°» ignored)</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 1 to overwrite a segment</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 2 to insert a segment</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 3 to delete a segment (in this case, variable « tabSeg » is not relevant)</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

	    <table>
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- TabSeg</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Array variable of 40 positions, instructions read are the following :</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 1 : sub side type (0 for straight, 1 for arch, 3 for ellipse).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 2 : X0 of segment.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 3 : Y0 of segment.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 4 : X1 of segment.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 5 : Y1 of segment.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 6 : X of center of the arch or first arch center in case of ellipse.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 7 : Y of center of the arch or first arch center in case of ellipse </span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 8 : X of center of second arch for ellipse.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 9 : Y of center of second arch for ellipse.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 10 : Arch radius.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 11 : « 0 » for an arch segment, « 1 » for a circle (Bull eye).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 12 : Arch rotation. « 1 » for anticlockwise, « 0 » for clockwise.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 28 : Defines a label for a segment (sub side in absolute), allows to fix an information to name a side 
				for instance.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 29 : Side label, Winpro side name. Useful to name sides in case of shrink for instance. See function <span
				class="f_Variables">ShapeSideInfo ()</span>.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
		style="text-decoration: underline;">Examples :</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp :
		40</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp:=
		0</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[2] := 870</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[3] := 1095</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[4] := 870</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[5] := 935</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[29] := 2</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
		style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">SetupShapeInfo
		(</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">100, 2,, 3, tmp</span><span
		style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">)</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
		style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">SetupShapeInfo
		(</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">100, 2, 10, 780</span><span
		style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">)</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp:
		30</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp:=
		0</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[1] := 1</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[2] := 160</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[3] := 1095</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[4] := 310</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[5] := 1095</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[6] := 160</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[7] := 1295</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[10] := 200</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[12] := 1</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp
		[29] := 4</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
		style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">SetupShapeInfo
		(</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">100, 2,, 2, toto</span><span
		style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">)</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
		style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">SetupShapeInfo
		(</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">100, 11,, 3, toto</span><span
		style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">)</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp :
		30</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
		style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp := 0</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp 
		[2] := 160</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp 
		[3] := 935</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp 
		[4] := 130</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp 
		[5] := 935</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp 
		[29] := 8</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
		style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">SetupShapeInfo
		(</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">100,,, 0, toto</span><span
		style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">)</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div
		style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="44"><span
				style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
			  </td>
			  <td><a name="ch3"></a><span
				style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">WinPro function for creation and modification of boards</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>Those functions allow creating and modifying the boards from a filling.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">ShrinkBoardShape (Shape index, Angle, LeftShrink, EndShrink, RightShrink, StartShrink)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Shrinks a board. Specifically designed for boards and transoms, but may be used with any shape, as soon as 2 sides are parallel 
		to <span class="f_Variables">Angle</span>.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape index to shrink into the shape array.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Angle</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape inclination (possible only if two sides are parallels).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- LeftShrink</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shrink for left side of the shape (oriented with the start in the back and the end in front of).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- EndShrink</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shrink for the end of the shape (oriented with the start in the back and the end in front of).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- RightShrink</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shrink for the right side of the shape (oriented with the start in the back and the end in front of).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- StartShrink</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shrink for the start of the shape (oriented with the start in the back and the end in front of).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">ConvertCurvesIntoLinesShape (Shape index, ConversionType)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Convert a complex shape into straight shape, contained or containing.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape to be converted</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- ConvesionType</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Type of conversion of the complex shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 0 result is shape containing the curves.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 1 result is shape contained into curves.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
		style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr align="left" valign="top">
			  <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
				style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
				style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">ConvertCurvesIntoLinesShape
				(</span><span
				style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">100,
				0</span><span
				style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">)</span></p>
			  </td>
			  <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
			  </td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img src="img/embim7.jpg" alt="" border="0"
		height="108" hspace="1" vspace="1" width="104"></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p><span
		style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"></span>Convert shape of index 100 into the shape array (circle, bulleye) into 
		containing shape.</p>

		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr align="left" valign="top">
			  <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
				style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span
				style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">ConvertCurvesIntoLinesShape
				(</span><span
				style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">100,
				1</span><span
				style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">)</span></p>
			  </td>
			  <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
			  </td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img src="img/embim8.jpg" alt="" border="0"
		height="106" hspace="1" vspace="1" width="115"></p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>Convert shape of index 100 into the shape array (circle, bulleye) into contained shape.</p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div
		style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="44"><span
				style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
			  </td>
			  <td><span
				style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">WinPro functions of computation results</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p class="p_Comment"><span
		style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

		<p>Those functions are designed to be able to interrogate the various shapes created in order to extract needed data.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">DebugShape (shapeNum)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Debug mode for a shape. WinPro's computation is stopped and a dialog displays the main properties of the shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
		style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr align="left" valign="top">
			  <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
				style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">DebugShape (</span><span
				class="f_Variables">TmpPanelGlobShapeNum</span><span
				class="f_Variables" style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>
			  </td>
			  <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
			  </td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p class="p_Comment" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img src="img/sssclip15eng.jpg"
		alt="sssClip15eng" border="0" height="596" width="424"></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>Debugs the shape of index « <span class="f_Variables">TmpPanelGlobShapeNum</span> » into the shape array.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">PointContainedIntoShape (Shape index, pointX, pointY)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Test if a point belongs to a shape or not.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape to be tested.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- PointX</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Coordinate "X" of the point to be tested.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- PointY</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Coordinate "Y" of the point to be tested.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>If <span class="f_Variables">ShapeInfo [28]</span> = -1   =&gt;   the point is outside the shape;</p>
		<p>If <span class="f_Variables">ShapeInfo [28]</span> = 0   =&gt;   the point is onto the shape's border;</p>
		<p>If <span class="f_Variables">ShapeInfo [28]</span> = 1   =&gt;   the point is within the shape.</p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">TestShape (Shape index)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>This instruction alows to know if a given shape is valid or not.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape to be tested.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>The variable <span class="f_Variables">ShapeInfo [3]</span> = 0 when the shape is invalid (number of segment = 0).</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">GetShapeInfo (Shape index, Side name, Side index, Sub side index)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Basic instruction that runs computation before using the next ones (<span class="f_Variables">ShapeInfo</span>, <span
		class="f_Variables">SideShapeInfo</span> and <span
		class="f_Variables">SubSideShapeInfo</span>).</p>

		<p>It is possible to query the overall shape, the overall shape and a side, the overall shape and a side and a sub-side. Accordingly, variables
		regarding shape details (<span class="f_Variables">ShapeInfo</span>), regarding the side of the shape (<span 
		class="f_Variables">SideShapeInfo</span>) and the sub-side of the shape (<span class="f_Variables">SubSideShapeInfo</span>) will be fulfilled or 
		not.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape number to be queried.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Side name</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Standard Winpro side (<span class="f_Variables">Top</span>, <span class="f_Variables">Bottom</span>, ..) to query. Side
				name or side number, but not at the same time. It is possible to leave the side (and sub-side too) unset, variables <span 
				class="f_Variables">SideShapeInfo</span> and <span class="f_Variables">SubSideShapeInfo</span> will the be left empty and return no value.
				Usefull to know only a global information about the shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Side index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Side number to query. Start at « 0 ». Side name or side number, not both. It is possible to leave the side (and
				sub-side too) unset, variables <span class="f_Variables">SideShapeInfo</span> and <span class="f_Variables">SubSideShapeInfo</span> will the
				be left empty and return no value. Usefull to know only a global information about the shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Sub side index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Sub side number into the side to be queried, starting at « 1 ». It is possible to leave the sub-side field unset, 
				the variable <span class="f_Variables">SubSideShapeInfo</span> will then return no value. Usefull to know only a global information about 
				the shape and the side.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

		<p>With a zero value, an array is filled with values from all sub side of a side, <span class="f_Variables">GetSubSideInfo</span>. For the « n » 
		sub side, the info labelled « i » is located into slot <span style="font-weight: bold;">(n-1) x 40 + i</span>.</p>

		<p>For instance, for a sub side, the first setting is rached with : <span style="font-weight: bold;">(n-1) x 40 +
		i = (1-1) x 40 + 1</span>.</p>

		<p>For 2 sub sides, setting 1 of sub side 2 : <span style="font-weight: bold;">(n-1) x 40 + i = (2-1) x
		40 + 1</span>.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
		style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr align="left" valign="top">
			  <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
				style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">GetShapeInfo (</span><span
				class="f_Variables">100,,,</span><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>
			  </td>
			  <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
			  </td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>This instruction runs the computation and set only the information variable for the shape, <span
		class="f_Variables">ShapeInfo</span>, for shape of index 100 from the shape array. Using this instruction, no side setting is needed, and then no
		sub-side too.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
		style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr align="left" valign="top">
			  <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
				style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">GetShapeInfo (</span><span
				class="f_Variables">1,,1,2</span><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>
			  </td>
			  <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
			  </td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>Computation is executed onto shape « 1 », the side number « 1 » and sub side number « 2 » (of side n°« 1 »). Global information of the shape is
		retrieved, along with side and sub side information.</p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">GenerateProfilesIntoShape (Shape index, Side name, Side index, Subside index , Start shape index, Middle shape
			  index, End shape index, Assembled shape index, Start assembly, End assembly, Previous subside thickness, Current subside thickness, Next 
			  subside thickness, Other subside thickness[, Start welding, End welding])</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>This instruction queries the shape. Variables 
		<span class="f_Variables">ShapeInfo</span>, <span
		class="f_Variables">SideShapeInfo</span> and <span
		class="f_Variables">SubSideShapeInfo</span> are fulfilled as for a <span
		class="f_Variables">GetShapeInfo</span> instruction, and shapes representing profiles are created, with assemblies and a set of information about the
		profile generated. The instruction carries 14 to 16 settings in case of welding value to consider or not.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p><span class="f_Variables">LastCreatedShapeNum [1]</span> returns the assembly shape for start of profile of sub side 1.</p>

		<p><span class="f_Variables">LastCreatedShapeNum [2]</span> returns the shape for middle of profile of sub side 1.</p>

		<p><span class="f_Variables">LastCreatedShapeNum [3]</span> returns the assembly shape for end of profile of sub side 1.</p>

		<p><span class="f_Variables">LastCreatedShapeNum [4]</span> returns the global shape of profile of sub side 1.</p>

		<p><span class="f_Variables">LastCreatedShapeNum [5]</span> returns the assembly shape for start of profile of sub side 2.</p>

		<p><span class="f_Variables">LastCreatedShapeNum [6]</span> returns the shape for middle of profile of sub side 2.</p>

		<p><span class="f_Variables">LastCreatedShapeNum [7]</span> returns the assembly shape for end of profile of sub side 1.</p>

		<p><span class="f_Variables">LastCreatedShapeNum [8]</span> returns the global shape of profile of sub side 1.</p>

		<p>And so on, as many times as sub sides.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of shape to query.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Side name</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Standard classique side name (<span class="f_Variables">Top</span>, <span class="f_Variables">Bottom</span>, ..) to
				query. Name or number of the side, but not both.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Side index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of side to query, starting at « 0 ». Name or number of the side, but not both.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Sub side index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of sub side into the side to query, starting at « 1 ». Value zero is a particular case even if widely used, as we
				search the most often to generate profiles for all subsides of the concerned side.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		
		<p>Refer to previous instruction.</p>

		<p>Next information for start, middle and end shapes, optional, are used to compute complex surface, related to thermic module for instance. The three
		following datas correspond to a shape index to store computed information. Usually, only the "overall shape of profile" is usefull for data set up.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
		style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

		<p class="p_Comment" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img src="img/embim9.jpg"
		alt="" border="0" height="131" hspace="1" vspace="1" width="513"></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>The computation for start shape and end shape correponds to a type 4 assembly join, whatever is the real assembly join. </p>

		<p>In case of impossible calculation, the next side returns the complement for the sum of all computed shapes for all sub sides to be equal to the
		real profile surface of the frame.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Example of join returning an impossible computation :</span></p>

