        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;">For a straight segment, [14] = [31] = [32], for a curved segment the 3 values are different. </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img
        src="img/sssclip16eng.jpg" alt="sssClip16eng" border="0" height="458"
        width="554"></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="44"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
              </td>
              <td><span
                style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">WinPro function of computation result for shape filling 
				« FWL »</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
        <p>Those functions are designed to query the shape array about the shape fillings in order to extract needed data.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">NbBoradCut</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Local variable returning the number of boards calculated, after running instruction 
		<span class="f_Variables">CuttingFWLShape ()</span>.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">GetBoardShapeInfo (Source shape index, Angle)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>This is suitable for any shape without running FWL initialization instruction. Anyway, the concerned shape must have 2 parallel sides at least, 
		and be composed of straight absolute segments (no bow).</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape index of the board that is to be queried for extracting computation result.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Angle</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Angle defined into instruction <span class="f_Variables">CuttingFWLShape ()</span>.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>Once instruction <span class="f_Variables">GetBoardShapeInfo ()</span> is run for a board (or a bar), function <span
        class="f_Variables">ShapeInfo ()</span> allows to know the various information about a board or a bar (array from 11 to 24).</p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [11]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">X0</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [12]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">Y0</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [13]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">X1</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [14]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">Y1</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [15]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">AngleSL</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [16]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">AngleSR</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [17]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">CuttingS</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [18]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">OffsetS</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [19]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">AngleEL</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [20]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">AngleER</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [21]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">CuttingE</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [22]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">OffsetE</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [23]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">TotalLength</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span style="font-style: italic;">* ShapeInfo [24]</span> returns « 
				<span class="f_Variables">ThicknessMax</span> ».</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="44"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
              </td>
              <td><a name="ch4"></a><span
                style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">WinPro functions for cutting shape</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>Those functions allow to consummate window elements (profiles, articles, labours, .).</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">ShapeNumToCut</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Used to consummate a shape for a filling (into panel rules for instance).</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 395px;" width="395"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 78px;"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">ShapeNumToCut </span><span
                style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">:= Shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td style="width: 679px;" width="679"><p>Consume the shape of specified index.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">DrawShape (Shape index, X, Y)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>This instruction allows to draw the outline of the defined shape into a WinPro drawing.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Examples :</span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 395px;" width="395"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">DrawShape (</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">1, 0, 0</span><span
                style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">)</p>
              </td>
              <td style="width: 679px;" width="679"><p>Draw shape of index 1 from the shape array at position (0,0).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>
		
        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;">or</p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 1200px;" width="1200"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
                style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">PenColour (_OuterFrameIntLineColourRed, _OuterFrameIntLineColourGreen, _OuterFrameIntLineColourBlue)</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 1200px;" width="1200"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
                style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">Brush (Colour, _OuterFrameIntColourRed, _OuterFrameIntColourGreen, _OuterFrameIntColourBlue)</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 1200px;" width="1200"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
                style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">StartPath ()</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 1200px;" width="1200"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">DrawShape (</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">1, 0, 0</span><span
                style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">)</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 1200px;" width="1200"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
                style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">EndPath ()</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr align="left" valign="top">
              <td style="width: 1200px;" width="1200"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
                style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">FillAndBorderPath ()</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';">This code draws shape of index 1 from the shape array, with line and fill 
		colour from outer frame.</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
        <div
        style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="44"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
              </td>
              <td><span
                style="font-size: 18pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Installation of a report for data exportation</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>A WPR report allows to retrieve the whole set of computed values and to export them toward 3 tables, <span
        style="font-style: italic;">ShapeInfo</span>, <span
        style="font-style: italic;">SideShapeInfo</span> and <span
        style="font-style: italic;">SubSideShapeInfo</span>.</p>

        <p>Data type « double », corresponding to values with decimals, are first multiplied by 1000000 into the code then returned to appropriate unit into
		export tables.</p>

        <p>This to keep a maximum of accuracy with decimals.</p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="44"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
              </td>
              <td><span
                style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">WpReport functions of shape definition/modification</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Those instructions are designed to generate shapes to be used into user defined 
		reports.</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: 
				rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">CreerTableauForme (n : Integer) : Boolean</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>This function creates the shape array. Into data set up the shape array is existing and is composed of 1000 slot, where the shape array needs to be
		defined manually into WPR, size included. First index is value « 1 ». The function returns <span class="f_Variables">True</span> or <span
        class="f_Variables">False</span> according the computation result.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- n</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Size of array.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-decoration: underline;">Examples :</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp_test1 := </span><span
        style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">CreerTableauForme(</span><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">100</span><span
        style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">)</span><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">;</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">if tmp_test1 = false then
        showmessage('computation error with function « CreerTableauForme »);</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>This WPR code creates a shape array with 100 cells, and returns an error message in case of problem.</p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: 
				rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">GetFreeShape (Setting)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>This function allows to know the first available cell from the shape array, Setting = 1. It returns value -1 when no shape is found. When a value
		of '-1' is used, the function returns the number of cells used within the shape array.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: 
				rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">DefinirInfoForme (Shape index, Segment index, Modification type, value)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>That's the function corresponding to <span class="f_Variables">SetupShapeInfo ()</span> with 4 settings from WinPro, as detailed above. It 
		allows defining or modifying various settings for a segment.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape to be modified.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Segment index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Segment index (sub side in absolute), starting at 0.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Modification type</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Type of modification to do. Attention, modification must always be finalized with closing the shape definition 
				(type « -100 »), but there is no need to start with granting modification of the shape as into WinPro's code.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 0 : Number of absolute sub segments.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 1 : Sub side type (0 for straight, 1 for bow, 3 for ellipse).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 2 : X0.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 3 : Y0.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 4 : X1.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 5 : Y1.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 6 : X of the bow center or of the first bow center in case of ellipse.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 7 : Y of the bow center or of the first bow center in case of ellipse.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 8 : X of the second bow center for an ellipse.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 9 : Y of the second bow center for an ellipse.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 10 : Bow radius.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 11 : Value « 0 » for an bow segment, « 1 » for a circle (Bull eye).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 12 : Bow rotation. « 1 » for anticlockwise, « 0 » for clockwise.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* -9 : Sets if the shape is opened (1) or closed (0).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* -10 : Forces or not the locking of position for computation. Remains unused usually, may corrupt computation in case of 
				bad use.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 28 : Defines a label for a segment (sub side in absolute), allows to fix an information to name a side for 
				instance.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 29 : Side label, Winpro side name. Useful to name sides in case of shrink for instance. See function 
				<span class="f_Variables">ShapeSideInfo ()</span>.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* -100 : Finalize the shape set up.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Examples :</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp_num_form := 10; </span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"> </span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp_test1 := </span><span
        style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">DefinirInfoForme (</span><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp_num_form,0,0,3</span><span
        style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">)</span><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">;</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);"> </span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp_test1 := </span><span
        style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">DefinirInfoForme (</span><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp_num_form,0,1,0</span><span
        style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">)</span><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">;</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp_test1 := </span><span
        style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">DefinirInfoForme (</span><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp_num_form,0,2,100</span><span
        style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">)</span><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">;</span></p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span
        style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">tmp_test1 := </span><span
