        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="44"><span
                style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
              </td>
              <td><a name="ch1"></a><span
                style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">WinPro shape testing function</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment"><span
        style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">SeekShapeTouchShape (shapeNum to test, Direction, Sashes shapes, Rectangle containing outer frame, Dimension
			  outside outer frame with false arch, TravIns, TravOut, TravTOT, User shape num)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>This function is suitable to test when shapes are touching one another. For instance, to test if a transom touches an outer frame side, or to test
		if a sash frame is in contact with an outer frame side.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- shapeNum to test</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Number of the shape to be tested.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Direction</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span class="f_ImageCaption">0
                = opposite direction, 1 = same direction, 2 = both directions (usually 2).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Sashes shapes</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Complete visible shape of each sash frame from the outer frame. That corresponds to the empty hole of each sash frame
				as seen into the outer frame.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Rectangle containing outer frame</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Rectangle containing the outer frame.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Dimension outside outer frame with false arch</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Outside outer frame shape including false arches shapes (almost the same shape as the previous one).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- TravIns</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Visible shape viewed from inside of a transom (smaller height visible from outer frame rebate only), appliable 
				for outer frame transom only.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- TravOut</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Visible shape viewed from outside of a transom (larger height from glass visible shape only),
                for outer frame transom only.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- TravTot</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Transom shape before milling
                (larger height from outer frame rebate), for outer frame transom only.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- User shape num</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">User shape number to be tested.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>The <span class="f_Variables">LastCreatedShape[]</span> variable will return the sequence number of shapes touching the tested/target shape, the 
        <span class="f_Variables">GetArraySize(LastCreatedShape)</span> will return the number of shapes touching the target shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>The array variable <span
        class="f_Variables">SettingsOfTouchedShape</span> will return the various datas from each shape touching the target shape, with a step of 40 cells :</p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 15px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;">from 1 to 17</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">for the first shape touching the tested shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 15px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;">from 41 to 57</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="514" style="width: 514px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">for the second shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 15px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;">...</span></p>
              </td>
              <td></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline">Setting
        1</span> =&gt; <span
        class="f_Variables">SettingsOfTouchedShape[1]</span> or <span
        class="f_Variables">SettingsOfTouchedShape[40 * xxx + 1]</span>
        returns the type of the touching shape.</p>

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">0</span> = Sash frame shape.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">1</span> = Shape of Rectangle containing outer frame.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">2</span> = Shape for outside outer frame dimension including false arch.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">3</span> = (TravIns)
                Transom shape as seen from inside (smaller height from outer frame rebate).</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">4</span> = (TravExt)
                Transom shape as seen from outside (largeur height from visible glass).</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">5</span> = (TravTot)
                Transom shape before milling (larger height from outer frame rebate).</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">6</span> = User shape.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline">Setting
        2</span> =&gt; Internal usage, for debug purpose only.</p>

        <p><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline">Setting
        3</span> =&gt; Sash index if the shape is a sash frame (variable
        <span class="f_Variables">SashIndex</span>).</p>

        <p><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline">Setting
        4</span> =&gt; Transom index if the shape is a transom (variable <span class="f_Variables">TransomIndex</span>).</p>

        <p><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline">Setting
        5</span> =&gt; Glazing type ; Glazing = 0, Plain panel = 1,
        Decorative panel = 2, Composed panel = 3, Decorative composed panel = 4.</p>

        <p><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline">Setting
        6</span> =&gt; Cutting type ; Transom = 0, Sash = 1,
        TransomAboveEmptyPart = 2, FrameAboveEmptyPart = 3.</p>

        <p><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline">Setting
        7</span> =&gt; Type of empty part, position of rebate ; Undefined =
        0, Inside = 1, Outside = 2, NoRebate = 3.</p>

        <p><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline">Setting
        10</span> =&gt; Returns a codification allowing detection of sides and sub sides touching one another between tested shape and found shape.</p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
        style="text-decoration: underline;">Examples :</span></p>

