        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">DeductShape (Source shape, Shape to deduct)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Deduct a defined shape from a source shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape to be modified, this shape will be overwritten.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape to deduct</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape that will be used as a mask.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;">

        <table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#bfd7bf"
        border="0"
        style="background-color: #bfd7bf; border: none border-spacing:0px; border-collapse: collapse;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="525"
                style="width: 525px; border: solid 1px #000000;"><p
                class="p_Notes" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 10px;"><span
                class="f_Notes" style="font-weight: bold;">Note</span><span
                class="f_Notes"> :</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- It is not possible to deduct a shape when included into another (make a hole).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
		style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr align="left" valign="top">
			  <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
				style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">DeductShape (</span><span
				class="f_Variables">1, 2</span><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>
			  </td>
			  <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
			  </td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>According below drawing, the source shape A is stored into shape array at index 1, the shape to be deducted is stored at index 1, the result shape
		C will be stored at index 1.</p>

		<p class="p_Comment" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img
		src="img/clip4-1.zoom60.jpg" alt="Clip4-1" border="0" height="298" width="319"></p>


        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">MergeShape (Source shape, Shape to merge)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Merge a defined shape to a source shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">The shape where the merge operation will be done, this shape will be modified.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape to merge</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape that will be merged to the first one. Attention, both shapes should share at least one segment.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;">

        <table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#bfd7bf"
        border="0"
        style="background-color: #bfd7bf; border: none border-spacing:0px; border-collapse: collapse;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="525"
                style="width: 525px; border: solid 1px #000000;"><p
                class="p_Notes" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 10px;"><span
                class="f_Notes" style="font-weight: bold;">Attention</span><span
                class="f_Notes"> :</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- Both shapes should share at least one common segment!</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
		style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr align="left" valign="top">
			  <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
				style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">MergeShape (</span><span
				class="f_Variables">1, 2</span><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>
			  </td>
			  <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
			  </td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>According below drawing, source shape A is stored into shape array at index 1, the B shape to merge is stored at index 2, and result shape is
		stored at index 1.</p>

		<p class="p_Comment" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img src="img/untitled.jpg"
		alt="Untitled" border="0" height="305" width="183"></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">IntersectionShape (Source shape, Shape to merge)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Merge a defined shape to a source shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape where the intersection is operated, this shape will be modified.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape to merge</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">The shape that will be merged with the first one.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span
		style="text-decoration: underline;">Example :</span></p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr align="left" valign="top">
			  <td style="width: 735px;" width="735"><p class="p_Comment"
				style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 66px;"><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">IntersectionShape (</span><span
				class="f_Variables">1, 2</span><span class="f_Variables"
				style="font-weight: bold;">)</span></p>
			  </td>
			  <td style="width: 339px;" width="339"><br>
			  </td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>According below drawing, source shape A is stored into the index 1 of the shape array, shape to merge B is stored at index 2, and result shape at
		index 1.</p>

		<p class="p_Comment" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img src="img/embim6.jpg"
		alt="" border="0" height="297" hspace="1" vspace="1" width="229"></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div
		style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="44"><span
				style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
			  </td>
			  <td><span
				style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">WinPro functions for creation and modification of shape filling 
				« FWL »</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>Those functions allow to compute fillings (glass units, panels, security bars.) of shapes created by previous functions defined, as it is 
		possible using functions FWL detailed into <a href="rn710x.php">release note version 7.1.00</a> (refer to FWL manual into main chm help file).</p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">CuttingFWLShape (Source shape index, Start target shape index, Angle, X, Y, CoefOffset, StartFlag, Thickness1,
			  Thickness2, Clamp1, Clamp2, NbBoardForced, SpacingMin, SpacingMax)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>This function defines filling options of a defined shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape index that needs to be filled using fillinf instructions (FWLs).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Start target shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of the shape for the first board or bar.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Angle</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Angle of the filling, between -89.9° and 90°.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- X</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Coordinate X of the reference point. Should be set only when StartFlag = 1, left value 0 otherwise.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Y</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Coordinate Y of the reference point. Should be set only when StartFlag = 1, left value 0 otherwise.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- CoefOffset </span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Coefficient allowing to modify the reference of start point proportionally to the dimension of board of thickness 1.
				Value between 1 and -1.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- StartFlag</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Reference point for position of the first board:</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 1 for point of coordinates {x,y}.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 2 for center of shape (difference between the uppest and lowest point, between the most on the left and
				the most on the right).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 3 reference point is the most on the left.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* 4 reference point is the most on the right.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="4000" style="width: 4000px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">* In case of negative value (-1, -2, -3, and -4), the shape is filled with bars instead of boards.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

