        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div
		style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 44px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="44"><span
				style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24pt; font-family: 'Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></span><br>
			  </td>
			  <td><span
				style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">WinPro function for cutting into sections a finished profile (shape)
				(!!! Enhancement of "BOWCut" functions !!!).</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p class="p_Comment"><span
		style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

		<p>Those functions are suitable to easier compute a bow cutting without various limitations. It is now possible to have bow parts and straight parts
		along onto the shape to cut, as well as concave and convex bows. See also functions <span class="f_Variables">BOWCutxxx ()</span> as defined into 
		<a href="rn722x.php">release note version 7.2.29</a>.</p>

		<p class="p_Comment"><span
		style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';"> </span></p>

		<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Those functions complete the following variables:</span><span>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17">
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">NbTrapeziumsCut -&gt; </span><span
				style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Number of trapeziums computed by the function.</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17">
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">AngleCutTrapezium -&gt; </span><span
				style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Array variable returning the slope of each trapezium. This allows to run a
				<span class="f_Variables">"GetBoardShapeInfo"</span> instruction easier to obtain the whole data from the trapezium.</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17">
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">CutShapeNum -&gt; </span><span
				style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman';">With the 10 settings version, this variable returns the index of shpe cutting
				created. The size of the array variable retuns the number of cutting sequences (or <span class="f_Variables">"NbTrapeziumsCut"</span> -
				1). </span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">4 possible syntaxes (7, 9, 10 and
		11 settings):</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">CutShapeIntoTrapeziums with 7
		settings:</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">CutShapeIntoTrapeziums (Source shape, Start destination shape, Nb trapezium mini, Nb trapezium
				maxi, Optimization time, Length mini, Penality)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>The most simple version, according a shape, the shape is cut with a number of trapeziums included between two limits.</p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of the shape to be cut into trapeziums. A closed shape with correct "labels" for the different sides is 
				required.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Start destination shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of the shape for the first computed trapezium (usually "-1"). May be left empty ",," to avoid storing 
				the trapezium shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Nb trapezium mini</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Minimum number of trapeziums to be obtained as a result. When mini = le maxi, the number of trapezium is 
				forced.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Nb trapezium maxi</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Maximum number of trapeziums to be obtained as a result. When mini = le maxi, the number of trapezium is 
				forced.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Optimization time</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">This value is set for the computation time available for each trapezium assembly. The minimum value is 1, 
				and there is no maximum value. Anyway for a modern computer, above a value of 50, the computation time start being disturbing for the 
				user.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Length mini</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Minimum length of a trapezium that is required, or average between outside and inside lengths of the 
				trapezium.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Penality</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Coefficient computed between the trapeziums surface and the surface of the shape to be cut. The weaker is the value,
				the most wastes are limited and then the greater the number of trapezium will be. (penality = 0 -&gt; for the maximum number of trapeziums). A
				safe basis is estimated to a value of 5000.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

