		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Examples :</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">GenerateProfilesIntoShape (...)</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">Quantity := 1</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128); font-weight: bold;">GenerateProfilesIntoShape (</span><span 
		style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">_Customer_BeadsShape,, i, 0, , , , - 1, Mitre, Mitre, 20, 20, 20, 20</span><span style="font-weight: bold;">)
		</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p>A profile is created here within shape of index "_Customer_BeadsShape", onto its side "i" for all subsides of side "0". The "Start", "Middle" and
		"End" shapes are not stored (value "0,0,0"), but the complete shape of each profile for subsides of the side. This is stored into the first available
		cell from the shape array "-1" for a start assembly as "Mitre", a end assembly type as "Mitre", with a previous profile of "20"mm, a current  profile
		of "20"mm , a next profile of "20"mm, and a value for others profiles of "20"mm (this profile "other" allows to manage with potential "side deletion
		within particular shapes")... No welding value set here.</p>

