		<p>This function allows, just afetr a profile generation, to consume it with setting the variables <span class="f_Variables">
		X0</span>, <span class="f_Variables">Y0</span>, <span class="f_Variables">X1</span>, <span class="f_Variables">Y1</span> , angles variables etc. 
		This for the whole subsides where the profile has been generated.</p>

		<p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Examples :</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">GenerateProfilesIntoShape (...)</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">Quantity := 1</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128); font-weight: bold;">ConsumeProfile ()</span></p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

