		</div>

		<p>Extract sub side(s) information from a shape of the shape array, after instruction <span class="f_Variables"><img
        src="OIForm.png" alt="OIF" border="0" height="20"
        width="20">GetShapeInfo ()</span> or <span class="f_Variables"><img
        src="GPDForm.png" alt="GPDF" border="0" height="20"
        width="20">GenerateProfilesIntoShape ()</span> into current code. Only information marked with corresponding sign are 
		generated by the instruction.</p>
		
        <p>When a query is made through instruction <span
        class="f_Variables">GetShapeInfo ()</span> with setting 0 for the sub side index, variable <span
        class="f_Variables">SubSideShapeInfo</span> avec les informations de
        tous les sous bords. is filled with information of all sub sides. To distinguish sub sides, indexes from 1 to 32 is for the first sub side (33 to 
		40 remains unused currently), 41 to 72 for the second (73 to 80 unused), etc.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">E.g. :</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">Searched index (1 to 32) + 40 * (sub side number - 1)</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128);">Then, for index 10 (bow radius) of sub side 2:</span></p>

		<p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 128); font-weight: bold;"><span class="f_Variables"
        style="font-weight: bold;">SubSideShapeInfo</span> <span class="f_Variables" style="font-weight: bold;">[</span>10 + 40 * (2
        &ndash; 1)<span class="f_Variables">]</span> = <span class="f_Variables" style="font-weight: bold;">SubSideShapeInfo [</span>50<span 
		class="f_Variables" style="font-weight: bold;">]</span>.</span></p>
				
