              <td><span class="f_Variables">SupprimerForme (N° de forme).</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>This functions purges shapes loaded into memory. For instance at the end of a routine using shapes for consumption and not for drawings, unused shapes may be 
		purged from the shape array.</p>
		
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: 
				rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">CopierForme (Source shape, Target shape)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Copy of source shape toward a target shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape index to be copied.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Target shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape index to be created.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">CouperForme (Source shape number, Left target shape number, Right target shape number, Angle, X Point, 
			  Y Point, Offset, Thickness)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>Cuts a shape according a given line.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;">

        <table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#bfd7bf"
        border="0"
        style="background-color: #bfd7bf; border: none border-spacing:0px; border-collapse: collapse;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="525"
                style="width: 525px; border: solid 1px #000000;"><p
                class="p_Notes" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 10px;"><span
                class="f_Notes" style="font-weight: bold;">Attention
                !</span><span class="f_Notes"> :</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- Take care when a closed shape is cut, the line should have 2 and only 2 crossing point with the shape. In case of opened shape, 1 point
				is enough.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape number</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape index that will be cut into the shape array.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Left target shape number</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Number of the left hand shape from the line that will be created for closed shape, or the start of an opened 
				shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Right target shape number</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Number of the right hand shape from the line that will be created for closed shape, or the end of an opened 
				shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Angle</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Inclination of the segment cutting the shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
           <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- X point</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">X coordinate of the point where the line crosses. (Into global bench mark).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Y point</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Y coordinate of the point where the line crosses. (Into global bench mark).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Offset</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Segment offset perpendicularly to itself (with an offset, the segment do not crosses XY coordinate anymore). Positive =
				on the right, Negative = on the left.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Thickness</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Segment thickness (like a saw blade), centered to the segment. No negative value allowed.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">CouperFormeParChemin (Source shape index, Left target shape index, Right target shape index, Cut shape index, 
			  labelL, labelR, ExtendBowCutWithStraight, doNotExtendCut)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>
				
        <p>Cut in two a given shape according a path defined by an opened shape, and generate a left shape, a right shape as well as the real cutting shape path.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;">

        <table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#bfd7bf"
        border="0"
        style="background-color: #bfd7bf; border: none border-spacing:0px; border-collapse: collapse;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="525"
                style="width: 525px; border: solid 1px #000000;"><p
                class="p_Notes" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 10px;"><span
                class="f_Notes" style="font-weight: bold;">Attention
                !</span><span class="f_Notes"> :</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- When left and right target shape " = 0", the "source" shape is not modified.</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- When a closed shape is cut, the cutting segment should have 2 and only 2 crossing points with the shape. In case of opened shape, a
				single point is enough.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape to be cut.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Left target shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of shape created on the left of cutting path for closed shapes, start of the opened shape otherwise.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- N° forme destination Droite</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of shape created on the right of cutting path for closed shapes, end of the opened shape otherwise.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Cut shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of opened shape containing the cutting path.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- labelL</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Label assigned to side created by the cutting within left shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- labelR</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Label assigned to side created by the cutting within right shape.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- ExtendBowCutWithStraight</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Allows to cut the shape using a "Bowed" segment at the end of the cut, in case the extension of the bow do not create a cutting point,
				the function then search if a point can be cerated by extending the segment.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
				- doNotExtendCut : True or false.
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- CheminNonProlonge</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">When set to true, the cutting path is not extended, whatever is the value of previous switch.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">TransformerForme (shapeNum, Transformation type, p1, p2, p3, p4)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p>Operates a transformation of the defined shape into another shape, using a translation, a proportional transformation, a rotation or a symmetry.</p>

        <p>Only specified Px settings are to be used, as an example for a type 1, do not leave the 2 last commas.</p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- shapeNum</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Index of the shape to be transformed.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Transformation type</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="800" style="width: 800px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption"></span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">1 : Translation using a vector (0,0), (p1, p2).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">2 : Proportional transformation of center (x,y) and factor (Fx, Fx). Uses settings p1, p2, p3.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">3 : Rotation of center (x,y)  and angle A. Uses settings p1, p2, p3.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">4 : Orthogonal symmetry based on line crossing points (x1,y1) and (x2,y2). Uses settings p1, p2, p3, p4.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">5 : Central symmetry of center (x1,y1). Uses settings p1, p2. This is equivalent to a proportional transformation
				(x1,y1,-1,-1), using settings p1, p2, p3, p4.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">SoustraireForme (Source shape, Shape to deduct)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Deduct a defined shape from a source shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape to be modified, this shape will be overwritten.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape to deduct</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape that will be used as a mask.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;">

        <table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#bfd7bf"
        border="0"
        style="background-color: #bfd7bf; border: none border-spacing:0px; border-collapse: collapse;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="525"
                style="width: 525px; border: solid 1px #000000;"><p
                class="p_Notes" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 10px;"><span
                class="f_Notes" style="font-weight: bold;">Note</span><span
                class="f_Notes"> :</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- It is not possible to deduct a shape when included into another (make a hole).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">UnionForme (Source shape, Shape to merge)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Merge a defined shape to a source shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">The shape where the merge operation will be done, this shape will be modified.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape to merge</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape that will be merged to the first one. Attention, both shapes should share at least one segment.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;">

        <table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#bfd7bf"
        border="0"
        style="background-color: #bfd7bf; border: none border-spacing:0px; border-collapse: collapse;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="525"
                style="width: 525px; border: solid 1px #000000;"><p
                class="p_Notes" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 10px;"><span
                class="f_Notes" style="font-weight: bold;">Attention</span><span
                class="f_Notes"> :</span><br>
                <span class="f_Notes">- Both shapes should share at least one common segment!</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		
		<div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

		<table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
		  <tbody>
			<tr valign="baseline">
			  <td width="17"><span
				style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
			  <td><span class="f_Variables">IntersectionForme (Source shape, Shape to merge)</span></td>
			</tr>
		  </tbody>
		</table>
		</div>

		<p>Merge a defined shape to a source shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Source shape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape where the intersection is operated, this shape will be modified.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape to merge</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">The shape that will be merged with the first one.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
