        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Array variable for segment values</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Array variable name that will be filled with information from segment of the shape. Same instruction as 
				<span class="f_Variables">ShapeSubSideInfo</span> in WinPro : Array of 33 cells (from 0 to 32, only below cells are filled).</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">1 : Sub side type (0 for straight, 1 for bow, 3 for ellipse).</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">2 : X0.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">3 : Y0.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">4 : X1.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">5 : Y1.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">6 : X of bow center or of first bow center in case of ellipse.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">7 : Y of bow center or of first bow center in case of ellipse.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">8 : X of center of second bow for an ellipse.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">9 : Y of center of second bow for an ellipse.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">10 : Bow radius.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">11 : « 0 » for a bow segment, « 1 » for a circle (Bull eye).</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">12 : Bow rotation, « 1 » for anticlockwise, « 0 » for clockwise.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">13 : Sub side length.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">14 : Sub side inclination (inclination of segment X0, Y0 ; X1, Y1)..</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">28 : Segment label du segment (sub side in absolute), 1000=start, 2000=outside, 3000=end, 4000=other.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">29 : Segment label, same as <span class="f_Variables">ShapeSideInfo [4]</span>.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">30 : Segment number.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">31 : DirectionStartSegment, tangent angle to the start point of the sub side.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="2500" style="width: 2500px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 50px;">32 : DirectionEndSegment, tangent angle to the end point of the sub side.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 48px;">For a straight segment, [14] = [31] = [32], for a curved one, all values are different.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <p class="p_Comment" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;"><img
        src="img/sssclip16eng.jpg" alt="sssClip16eng" border="0" height="458"
        width="554"></p>
		
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: 
				rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">DebugForme (Shape index)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>This function mainly allows, when writing a report in debug mode, displaying of information about the shape.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Shape index</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape that should be queried.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: 
				rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">ShapeToSVG (withStartTag, Width,
                Height, Title, numShape, withEndTag)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>This function returns the text of a SVG drawing (free vector drawing format, Scalar Vector Graphic).</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- WithStartTag</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Write SVG file header.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Width</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">SVG drawing width. Only used into header, ignored elsewhere. A null (0) value may be used without involving error.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Height</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">SVG drawing length. Only used into header, ignored elsewhere. A null (0) value may be used without involving error.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Title</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Drawing title. Only used into header, ignored elsewhere. An empty string value may be used without involving error.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- NumShape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape index to draw. A -1 value allows generating an empty shape without getting an error, which allow to continue with next SVG 
				filling instructions.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- WithEndTag</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Write header of SVG file.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

        <div
        style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px;">

        <table style="line-height: normal;" border="0" cellpadding="0"
        cellspacing="0">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="baseline">
              <td width="17"><span
                style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'Arial Unicode MS','Lucida Sans Unicode','Arial'; color: 
				rgb(0, 0, 255);">&bull;</span></td>
              <td><span class="f_Variables">ShapeToDXF (withStartTag, numShape,
                Layer, color, withEndTag)</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        </div>

        <p>This function returns the text of a DXF drawing file.</p>

        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>

		<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"
        style="border: none border-spacing:0px;">
          <tbody>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- WithStartTag</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Write header of DXF file.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- NumShape</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Shape index to be drawn. A -1 value allows generating an empty shape without getting an error, which allow to continue with next 
				DXF filling instructions.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Layer</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Name of the layer.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- Color</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Colour of the element. 0 =&gt; same colour as the block; 256 =&gt; same colour as the layer. 1 à 255 =&gt; index of
				the colour; negative =&gt; layer is hidden.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top" align="left">
              <td width="229" style="width: 229px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 23px;"><span
                style="font-style: italic;">- WithEndTag</span></p>
              </td>
              <td width="1200" style="width: 1200px;"><p
                style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;"><span
                class="f_ImageCaption">Write header of DXF file.</span></p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>


        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
        <p class="p_Comment"> </p>
		</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
